verbose_text: The primary endpoint at 24 months postsurgery related to the proportion of patients experiencing one of the following symptoms : constipation (1 stool/> 5 consecutive days), frequent bowel movements (> = 3 stools / day), defecation pain, anal incontinence (involuntary loss of gas or stools), dysuria (urinary symptom profile (USP) score for dysuria> = 1) or bladder atony requiring bladder voiding by self catheterization.
